<HEADLINE>
CAL STATE NORTHRIDGE BACK INJURED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JILL PAINTER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Cal State Northridge sophomore running back Alan
Taylor was diagnosed with a fractured left fibula and is expected
to be out 8-10 weeks most if not all of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor, who was injured on the third play of Saturday's
scrimmage, was the Matadors' only experienced running back of the
four players competing for the starting spot.
</P>
<P>
   CSUN opens Saturday at Air Force. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
