   PACKARD (Undated) {ndash} A Phoenix man puts up for auction the
rights to the famous Packard automobile name, along with the
prototype car he built hoping to resurrect the company. The Packard
Motor Car Company goes on the block in Auburn, Ind., at the Kruse
International classic car auction, and on eBay, which owns Kruse.
By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
