enterprise by people who claim their civil rights were violated
LAPD officers. The ruling creates the possibility that the
department could be the first in the nation to face trial under the
Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations law. It also could
dramatically increase the city's liability. By Don Terry.
</P>
<P>
   IMMIG-DEPORT (Undated) _ Like phantoms barreling down from a
hazy, distant past, ancient crimes and misdemeanors, sometimes
decades old, have been dredged up by Immigration and Naturalization
Service investigators to condemn tens of thousands of immigrants to
hasty and usually irrevocable deportation proceedings. The
magnitude of the crime is irrelevant. If it is considered an
aggravated felony _ shoplifting can be an aggravated felony _ the
immigrants must go. By Chris Hedges. (1500 words)
</P>
