</P>
<P>
   Two decades later, plans to build a car parking lot over the
sacred tomb were hastily reconsidered after terrified city
officials, not to mention repeated accidents, made the sacrilegious
American occupying forces think twice.
</P>
<P>
   Even today, superstitious office workers in nearby banks and
trading firms avoid turning their desks and backs disrespectfully
to the tomb.
</P>
<P>
   Masakado's ghost is not alone in Tokyo. The city has always had
its haunted places and wandering souls, and Tokyoites remain a
