   SAFRICA-RACISM (Roodepoort, South Africa) _ Six years after the
end of apartheid, South Africa is about to embark on its first
examination of racism across all segments of society. A four-day
conference will serve as a dress rehearsal for a UN global
conference on racism to be held next year. By Kurt Shillinger. 1000
