   CAMPAIGN (Portland, Maine) _ George W. Bush accuses Al Gore of
being stuck in the past by offering proposals, such as expanded
health-care coverage, that the administration should have been
addressing in the past seven years. Gore offers a child health-care
plan in New Mexico. By Glen Johnson and Anne E. Kornblut. 1200
words.
