   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MA-SAT (Boston) _ New SAT results show Massachusetts' combined
math and verbal scores are up 8 points since 1998. Girls in
particular saw their math scores rise, welcome news to those
worried about a gender gap. And Massachusetts is among the top four
states in the number of students who take the SAT. By Scott
Greenberger. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-CENSUS-BABIES (Boston) _ White babies, which once made up the
majority of births in Greater Boston, are now in the minority
category. In fact, black children alone outnumber white children in
all age categories, according to US Census statistics. By Cindy
Rodriguez. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   JFK-GIJOE (Boston) _ With fanfare and flourishes, and Hasbro
hovering nearby, JFK will again be inducted into a place of honor
at the JFK Library, this time as a GI Joe action figure. By Chris
Reidy. 700 words.
</P>
