wife Patricia, as a new book claims. But plenty of evidence on the
record shows that during the White House years the Nixons had a
chilly relationship. Pat Nixon was probably the last president's
spouse in modern history to be ignored and pushed aside by her
husband. By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   HINES-COLUMN (Washington) _ Sen. Joseph Lieberman's deep
religious conviction is one of his most appealing aspects. As a
continuing theme in Lieberman's national campaign, it is quickly
losing its charm. Lieberman moved up to the line and probably
crossed it in remarks Sunday in Detroit, as he began his first solo
campaign swing as the Democratic vice presidential candidate. By
CRAGG HINES. (Already filed.)
