<P>
   DLJ-CREDIT-SUISSE (New York) _ Folo on reports that Donaldson,
Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette is in talks to be sold to a larger rival, Credit
Suisse First Boston. An acquisition by Credit Suisse of DLJ, would
be the second buyout of a Wall Street firm by a Swiss bank this
summer. It would combine First Boston, a leading underwriter of
technology stocks, with DLJ, the longtime leader in underwriting
high-yield, or ``junk,'' bonds. By Patrick McGeehan.
</P>
<P>
   (With photo NYT22 and graphic.)
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 9 p.m.)
