<P>
   TRANSMETA-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ In January, a semiconductor
company called Transmeta promised to make laptop computer batteries
that would last a full work day. Though it is still months away
from its planned delivery date, Transmeta has since signed deals
with prominent computer makers, including IBM and Sony, and has
filed for an initial public offering of its stock.
</P>
