<SLUG> BC-RAMSEYS0830-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA - After two days of voluntary questioning by police,
Patsy Ramsey said she believes authorities still suspect her of
killing her daughter, JonBenet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think they still have doubt,'' said Patsy Ramsey in a press
conference outside her attorney's office Tuesday. ``They've been
down this road so long that I don't know that one or two mornings
talking with them will make an abrupt about-face.''
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday concluded John and Patsy Ramsey's first interviews with
Boulder, Colo., police in two years. Police interviewed Patsy for
more than seven hours and John Ramsey for about two and a half
hours. Despite a nearly 4-year investigation, no one has been
charged in the murder of the Ramseys' 6-year-old daughter in
Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Ramsey attorney Lin Wood called on police to issue a
statement clearing the couple.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
