<HEADLINE>
RUDY'S BLUNDER, OTHER `SURVIVOR' NOTES
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By LISA DAVIS 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   RICHIE'S RICH: Rudy, Rudy, Rudy. If only you'd kept your hand on
the immunity idol! But the guy everybody wanted to win ``Survivor''
made a stupid mistake, and instead the million dollars went to the
devious Richard. On the post-finale special with Bryant Gumbel,
Rich said he wants to use the money to start an adventure camp for
troubled teens (where, presumably, they would be forced to go
jogging at 4 a.m.).
</P>
<P>
   Ah, well. Better Rich than Kelly, who came in a close second. As
Colleen said, casting a reluctant vote for the tongue-pierced river
guide, ``Maybe this will make you nice.'' (Personal note to Kelly:
When one is appearing on a
live TV special, it is proper etiquette to KEEP YOUR SHOES ON.)
</P>
<P>
   So what do we do now? For starters, we can hope that Rudy's
application to ``Survivor II'' will be approved.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LINE OF THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   ``This island is full of two things: snakes and rats. And now we
have come to the final vote, between Richard the snake and Kelly
the rat.''
</P>
<P>
   _ the ever-tactful Susan, addressing her former alliance members
before the final ``Survivor'' vote
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BULLISH
</P>
<P>
   1. Villains: Brutal Sue, back-stabbing Kelly, Machiavellian
Richard ... we don't like them, and now we've made them famous.
</P>
<P>
   2. The Rich Dance: Rich shakes his groove thang on a hit Web
site. The Hamster Dance meets the Dancing Baby.
</P>
<P>
   3. Australia: Between the Olympics and ``Survivor II,'' it's the
place to be. It almost makes up for ``Crocodile Dundee.''
</P>
<P>
   4. The rice diet: It worked for Rich, who lost 34 pounds in 39
days!
</P>
<P>
   5. Jenna: She turned down an offer to pose for ``Playboy.''
Enough exposure, already.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BEARISH
</P>
<P>
   1. Anne Heche: After breaking up with Ellen DeGeneres, she was
found wandering aimlessly, tired, thirsty, babbling and wearing
only a bra and shorts. Was she auditioning for ``Survivor II''?
</P>
<P>
   2. Superpole 2000: Sean's overrated fishing rod was
unceremoniously burned by Rich and Kelly.
</P>
<P>
   3. Bryant Gumbel: If he had any journalistic integrity left, the
smarmy job he did hosting ``Survivor: The Reunion'' did away with
it.
</P>
<P>
   4. The Reebok Guys: Vote them off the island. Now.
</P>
<P>
   5. Wednesday nights: Now what are we going to watch?
</P>
<P>
   _
